:: 20_astory-text-eng [nobr]

<<timed 0.1s>>
    <<replace "#processingMount">>
        <<include "processing">>
        <</replace>>
        <</timed>>
 <<timed 0.1s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
        <iframe width="100%" height="640" frameborder="0" allow="xr-spatial-tracking; gyroscope; accelerometer" allowfullscreen scrolling="no" src="https://kuula.co/share/collection/7Dswj?logo=1&info=1&fs=1&vr=0&sd=1&thumbs=1"></iframe>

<div class="quote"><p>"I do think people wondered why there's this theatre and television studio up the hill, you know, yes, I do think people wondered about that, but whoever had the vision, I think, had a wonderful, wonderful vision of what was to come."</p></div>
<p class="bold">That’s Christine Langton – wife of the late Maurice Langton – who in 1975 got the job to design and manage where you are now: Theatr Clwyd’s old TV studio.  </p>
    <</append>>
<</timed>>

 <<timed 27s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
<p>It’s a huge, soundproofed room, with very high ceilings. Hanging from the ceiling is the lighting grid, which still has many of the old numbers and details. The bars are boxy and dark grey and I can imagine heavy lights hanging from them, filling the room with a strange buzz.  </p>
    <</append>>
<</timed>>
 <<timed 44s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
<p>This is actually part of what was a pantograph system - which would have channeled electricity into the room, powering the lights, and the systems, everything that was used to make the TV shows here. </p> 
<p>It’s changed now - but the bars are what would have made everything possible. </p>
  <</append>>
<</timed>>
 <<timed 56s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
<div class="quote"><p>"The studio complex became an object of pride, really, for that area...TV was actually made from Mold. In the village that I lived in. People were dumbfounded by the idea that there was a television station studio down the road, and they were delighted, actually. So, oh, this, this actually means something to us." </p></div>

<p>That’s John Hunter – a TV director and producer, who worked here as an HTV cameraman. </p>
  
<p>This room has had quite a history. It began life as part of an education technology centre for schools, where local young people could make films. </p>
  <</append>>
<</timed>>


<<timed 98s>>
