<<timed 0.1s>>
    <<replace "#processingMount">>
        <<include "processing">>
        <</replace>>
        <</timed>>
<<timed 0.1s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
   
<p class="bold">Then it became Studio 2 – a home in North Wales for two TV channels that mean a lot to Welsh people – HTV and S4C. </p>
<p>They created music programmes, chat shows and quizzes, with audiences bussed in by the coachload. The beloved Welsh-language children’s programme Ffalabalam – and its beautiful sets, full of little houses and toys – was made here, too.</p> 
  <</append>>
<</timed>>


<<timed 22s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
<div class="quote"><p class="bold">"Ffalabalam was a completely charming children's programme. It was, it was a beauty of a programme and I don't know why it ended to be honest. A small village as one imagines, such as the miniature villages one gets in the Cotswolds etc. The set was amazing with dolls and teddies and to tell the truth, they were the characters, except that we as presenters kind of understood them talking even though they didn't say anything and we conveyed the programme through that."</p></div>
  <</append>>
<</timed>>
<<timed 53s>>
    <<append "#msgMount">>
<p>That’s Welsh TV royalty Caryl Parry Jones – a singer, actor and she was a presenter at HTV and S4C – and clearly a fan of <i>Ffalabalam</i>. </p>
  <</append>>
<</timed>>
<<timed 65s>>
