<p class="bold">Here we are.</p> 
<p>This room is wide and very tall, extending below and above where we stand. Bits of design and construction for future shows are often dotted around. And every time you come in, it’s different. A prop, a costume, some sketches. This is the room where the designer's dreams are made real.  </p>

<p>And the Paint Frame is monumental. Katy Salt can tell us more about this amazing part of Theatr Clwyd. </p>
<p>She first painted the pantomime in 2001 – she knows how the paint frame works better than anyone.</p>
  <</append>>
<</timed>>
<<timed 33s>>
