     <<append "#msgMount">>
        <p class="bold">And we have another one coming through.</p>
<div class="quote">
<p>The first time I remember going to Theatr Clwyd was when I was in a production of Oliver when I was around 15 and I remember being on stage and it was total magic. It’s an amazing theatre and I’ve been very fortunate growing up in Mold. So later on, I was part of a group called Cwmni 25 and I did a lot of workshops for young people during the summer.</p>

<p>With Cwmni 25, run by Gwennan Mair Jones, I was really lucky that she was running the sessions bilingually, naturally bilingually, so that was my first introduction to the Welsh arts scene.</p>

</div>
 <</append>>
<</timed>>
<<timed 51s>>
     <<append "#msgMount">>
<p>That’s Isabella Colby Browne – another actor from Mold – she first performed in a production of Oliver on the stage when she was 15. Thanks to a group called Cwmni 25, run by Gwennan Mair Jones. She went on to perform in Welsh and English! Da iawn Isabella. </p>
 <</append>>
<</timed>>


